{"title_page": "1991 FIFA Women's World Cup Group A", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n'''Group A of the [[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup]]''' took place from 16 to 21 November 1991. The group consisted of hosts [[China women's national football team|China PR]], [[Denmark women's national football team|Denmark]], [[New Zealand women's national football team|New Zealand]] and [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Shannon |first=David |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesw/wwc91f.html |title=Women's World Cup 1991 (China) |website=RSSSF.com |publisher=[[RSSSF|Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |date=25 June 2015 |access-date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Standings==\n{{1991 FIFA Women's World Cup group tables|Group A}}\n\n==Matches==\nAll times listed are local, [[Time in China|CST]] ([[UTC+08:00|UTC+8]]).\n\n===China PR vs Norway===\n<section begin=A1 />{{Football box\n|date={{Start date|1991|11|16|df=y}}\n|time=20:45\n|team1={{fbw-rt|CHN}}\n|score={{score link|1991 FIFA Women's World Cup Group A#China PR vs Norway|4\u20130}}\n|report=https://www.fifa.com/womensworldcup/matches/round=1309/match=22004/index.html\n|team2={{fbw|NOR}}\n|goals1=\n*[[Ma Li (footballer)|Ma Li]] {{goal|22}}\n*[[Liu Ailing]] {{goal|45||50}}\n*[[Sun Qingmei]] {{goal|75}}\n|goals2=\n|stadium=[[Tianhe Stadium]], [[Guangzhou]]\n|attendance=65,000<ref name=\"TR91\">{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/afdeveloping/technicaldevp/50/08/19/wwc_91_tr_part2_260.pdf |title=1st FIFA World Championship for Women's Football for the M&M's Cup China '91 \u2013 Technical Report |website=FIFA.com |publisher=[[FIFA|F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association]] |access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n|referee=[[Salvador Imperatore]] ([[Football Federation of Chile|Chile]])\n}}<section end=A1 />\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"40%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size:90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=25| !!width=25|\n|-\n