nited States women's national soccer team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1991 Fifa Womens World Cup Final}}\n[[Category:1991 FIFA Women's World Cup|Final]]\n[[Category:FIFA Women's World Cup Finals|1991]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Guangzhou|Fifa World Cup Final 1991]]\n[[Category:United States women's national soccer team matches|1991]]\n[[Category:Norway at the 1991 FIFA Women's World Cup|World Cup]]\n[[Category:United States at the 1991 FIFA Women's World Cup| ]]\n[[Category:Norway women's national football team matches|1991]]\n[[Category:November 1991 sports events in Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox football match\n| title            = 1991 FIFA Women's World Cup Final\n| image            = Tianhe Stadium.jpg\n| image_size       = 250\n| caption          = Tianhe Stadium in Guangzhou hosted the final.\n| event            = [[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup]]\n| team1            = [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]]\n| team1association = {{flagdeco|NOR|size=30px}}\n| team1score       = 1\n| team2            = [[United States women's national soccer team|United States]]\n| team2association = {{flagdeco|USA|size=30px}}\n| team2score       = 2\n| details          =\n| date             = {{Start date|1991|11|30|df=y}}\n| stadium          = [[Tianhe Stadium]]\n| city             = [[Guangzhou]]\n| referee          = [[Vadim Zhuk]] {{nowrap|([[Football Federation of the Soviet Union|Soviet Union]])}}\n| attendance       = 63,000<ref name=\"TR\"/>\n| weather          =\n| next             = [[1995 FIFA Women's World Cup Final|1995]]\n}}\nThe '''1991 FIFA Women's World Cup Final''' was a [[Association football|football]] match that took place on 30 November 1991 at [[Tianhe Stadium]] in [[Guangzhou]], [[China]]. It was played between [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]] and the [[United States women's national soccer team|United States]] to determine the winner of the [[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/womensworldcup/chinapr1991/index.html |title=FIFA Women's World Cup \u2013 China PR 1991 |work=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |accessdate=26 August 2014}}</ref> The United States beat Norway 2\u20131, with two goals from [[Michelle Akers|Michelle Akers-Stahl]], to become winners of the first ever [[FIFA Women's World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Combating a myth from Women's World Cup '91 |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/inside_game/michael_lewis/news/1999/07/14/myth_destroyed/ |work=Sports Illustrated |date=14 July 1999 |accessdate=1 August 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000819070550/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/inside_game/michael_lewis/news/1999/07/14/myth_destroyed/ |archivedate=19 August 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Barbara |last=Basler |title=American women in final in soccer |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/11/28/sports/american-women-in-final-in-soccer.html |work=The New York Times |date=28 November 1991 |accessdate=30 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThe final was contested by [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]], who rebounded from a stunning 4\u20130 defeat by host nation [[China women's national football team|China PR]] to qualify from their group. They then dispatched [[Italy women's national football team|Italy]] and historic rivals [[Sweden women's national football team|Sweden]] in the knockout rounds to reach the final. The other team in the final was the [[United States women's national soccer team|United States]], who went undefeated throughout the competition, thrashing highly rated [[Germany women's national football team|Germany]] 5\u20132 in the semi-final.<ref>{{cite news |first=Barbara |last=Basler |title=Soccer; U.S. women beat Norway to capture World Cup |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/12/01/sports/soccer-us-women-beat-norway-to-capture-world-cup.html |work=The New York Times |date=1 December 1991 |accessdate=1 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Barbara |last=Basler |title=Sports Weekend; U.S. women's soccer team's message: 'No one will get in our way' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/11/29/sports/sports-weekend-us-women-s-soccer-team-s-message-no-one-will-get-in-our-way.html?src=pm |work=The New York Times |date=29 November 1991 |accessdate=1 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Route to the final==\n{|  style=\"width:100%; text-align:center;\"\n|-  style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#9cf;\"\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|Norway\n!Round\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|United States\n|-  style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#c1e0ff;\"\n|Opponent\n|Result\n||[[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup#Group Stage|Group stage]]\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|-\n|align=left|{{fbw|PRC}}\n|0\u20134\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|Match 1\n|align=left|{{fbw|SWE}}\n|3\u20132\n|-\n|align=left|{{fbw|NZL}}\n|4\u20130\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|Match 2\n|align=left|{{fbw|BRA}}\n|5\u20130\n|-\n|align=left|{{fbw|DEN}}\n|2\u20131\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|Match 3\n|align=left|{{fbw|JPN}}\n|3\u20130\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n<center>{{1991 FIFA Women's World Cup group tables|Group A|only_pld_pts=yes|showteam=NOR}}</center>\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|Final standings\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n<center>{{1991 FIFA Women's World Cup group tables|Group B|only_pld_pts=yes|showteam=USA}}</center>\n|-  style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#c1e0ff;\"\n|Opponent\n|Result\n||[[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup#Knockout stage|Knockout stage]]\n|Opponent\n|Result\n|-\n|align=left|{{fbw|ITA}}\n|3\u20132 \n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|[[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup#Quarterfinals|Quarter-finals]]\n|align=left|{{fbw|TPE|football-old}}\n|7\u20130\n|-\n|align=left|{{fbw|SWE}}\n|4\u20131\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|[[1991 FIFA Women's World Cup#Semifinals|Semi-finals]]\n|align=left|{{fbw|GER}}\n|5\u20132\n|}\n\n==Match==\n\n===Details===\n